## How the engines work (short version)}
\par \pard\plain \s20\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\sb0\sa0\f4\fs20\dbch\af7\ql\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\loch

\par \pard\plain \s20\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\sb0\sa0\f4\fs20\dbch\af7\ql\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\loch
- **ZigZag engine** \u8212\'97 detects swing highs and lows with strict high \u8594\'3f low \u8594\'3f high alternation, so the structure is always clean.}
\par \pard\plain \s20\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\sb0\sa0\f4\fs20\dbch\af7\ql\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\loch
- **Structure engine** \u8212\'97 labels each swing as HH (higher high), LH (lower high), HL (higher low), or LL (lower low) using the standard market-structure definition.}
\par \pard\plain \s20\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\sb0\sa0\f4\fs20\dbch\af7\ql\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\loch
- **Trend engine** \u8212\'97 looks at the last confirmed HH/LH and HL/LL pair to decide bullish, bearish, or consolidation per timeframe.}
\par \pard\plain \s20\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\sb0\sa0\f4\fs20\dbch\af7\ql\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\loch
- **MTF S/R engine** \u8212\'97 extracts support and resistance from 15M, 1H and 4H, applies the S/R flip rule (resistance is always above price, support always below), and filters by proximity.}
\par \pard\plain \s20\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\sb0\sa0\f4\fs20\dbch\af7\ql\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\loch
- **BOS / CHOCH engines** \u8212\'97 detect break-of-structure and change-of-character events that signal trend continuation or reversal.}
\par \pard\plain \s20\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\sb0\sa0\f4\fs20\dbch\af7\ql\sb0\sa0\ltrpar{\loch
- **Session engine** \u8212\'97 overlays the Asian (00\u8211\'9609 UTC), London (08\u8211\'9617 UTC), and New York (13\u8211\'9622 UTC) sessions, including their natural overlap windows.}
\par \pard\plain \s20\rtlch\af4\afs20 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\sb0\sa0\f4\fs20\dbch\af7\ql\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\loch

